{"type":"message","id":"cf296be9","parentId":"8b2f33cb","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:56:49.416Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the most recent pulse log (155617) and also check the mutation that was created.","thinkingSignature":"59b1c45047f5932b27157f745a3571259392743b8ab3228805da4db5c07e846b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hxr3044gzm7y_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 155617.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hxr3044gzm7y_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\research\\ -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object Name"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2065,"output":120,"cacheRead":12245,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14430,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774382205697}}
{"type":"message","id":"9de47a98","parentId":"cf296be9","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:56:49.617Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_hxr3044gzm7y_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 155617\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/HYBRID_SCORING_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the most impactful action for this pulse.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals and recent synthesis:\r\n\r\n1. **CFI Compression Experiment is COMPLETE** - we have the analysis showing CFI×Freq hybrid is the right approach\r\n2. **Next immediate step**: Run the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n   - Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n   - Test against binary thresholds\r\n   - 200 pulses, 80/20 split\r\n\r\nThe key insight is that the \"Constant Format Problem\" tokens (freq=160, CFI=1) are metaprogramming artifacts that need to be filtered. The hybrid formula should distinguish these from true research trajectory tokens.\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next action is to **implement and run the hybrid scoring experiment**. This directly follows from the CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md findings.\r\n\r\nI should:\r\n1. Create a pulse analysis script that implements the hybrid scoring\r\n2. Run it on the 200 pulses\r\n3. Compare results against binary thresholds\r\n\r\nOr, I could update the research document to specify the exact experimental design for the next phase, making the pending task concrete.\r\n\r\nGiven that I'm a stateless agent and need to make progress, let me create a concrete experiment spec that can be executed.\r\n\r\nActually, the most efficient single action would be to:\r\n1. Create an experiment runner script that implements the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring\r\n2. This script will process the pulses and generate comparison data\r\n\r\nLet me create `research/cfi_hybrid_experiment.ps1` that implements Strategy C vs the binary threshold strategies.\r\n\r\nWait, I should check what scripts exist. Looking at the context:\r\n- `pulse.ps1` - the main pulse script\r\n- We have `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md` with the analysis\r\n\r\nThe most direct action: implement the hybrid scoring experiment to test whether score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) actually distinguishes constant-format from research-trajectory tokens.\r\n\r\n\r\nI'll craft a PowerShell script to validate the hybrid scoring approach, focusing on extracting precise token characteristics across the pulse dataset.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI Compression Synthesis identified the \"Constant Format Problem\" - tokens with freq=160, CFI=1.0 are metaprogramming artifacts, not true causal patterns. The next concrete step is to implement and test Strategy C: the hybrid scoring formula.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `research/cfi_hybrid_experiment.ps1` - a script that implements the hybrid scoring formula `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` and runs a comparison against binary thresholds on the existing 200-pulse dataset. This directly tests whether the hybrid approach distinguishes constant-format from research-trajectory tokens.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```powershell\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI Hybrid Scoring Experiment - Strategy C vs Binary Thresholds\r\n# Based on: CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md findings\r\n# Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n# Hypothesis: Hybrid scoring distinguishes constant-format (freq~160, CFI~1) from research trajectory (freq<120, CFI>0.5)\r\n\r\n$pulseDir = \"state/pulses\"\r\n$outputFile = \"research/cfi_hybrid_results.md\"\r\n\r\n# Ensure output directory exists\r\n$pulses = Get-ChildItem $pulseDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | Sort-Object Name | Select-Object -First 200\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"CFI Hybrid Scoring Experiment\"\r\nWrite-Host \"================================\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Testing: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Dataset: $($pulses.Count) pulses\"\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\n\r\n# Aggregate token statistics across all pulses\r\n$tokenStats = @{}\r\n\r\nforeach ($pulse in $pulses) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $pulse.FullName -Raw\r\n    $tokens = [regex]::Matches($content, '\\S+') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value }\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($token in $tokens) {\r\n        if (-not $tokenStats.ContainsKey($token)) {\r\n            $tokenStats[$token] = @{\r\n                Count = 0\r\n                Occurrences = @()\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        $tokenStats[$token].Count++\r\n        $tokenStats[$token].Occurrences += $pulse.Name\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Calculate CFI and frequency for each token\r\n$analysisResults = @()\r\n$totalTokens = $tokenStats.Values | Measure-Object -Property Count -Sum | Select-Object -ExpandProperty Sum\r\n\r\nforeach ($entry in $tokenStats.GetEnumerator()) {\r\n    $token = $entry.Key\r\n    $stats = $entry.Value\r\n    $freq = $stats.Count\r\n    $occurrences = $stats.Occurrences\r\n    \r\n    # CFI: tokens that appear in EXACTLY the same pulse set\r\n    # Approximation: count how many other tokens share identical occurrence patterns\r\n    $patternKey = ($occurrences | Sort-Object) -join \",\"\r\n    $matchingPatterns = $tokenStats.Values | Where-Object { \r\n        ($_.Occurrences | Sort-Object) -join \",\" -eq $patternKey \r\n    } | Measure-Object\r\n    \r\n    $cfi = [math]::Round($matchingPatterns.Count / $tokenStats.Count, 4)\r\n    \r\n    # Hybrid score: CFI × normalized frequency\r\n    $normalizedFreq = [math]::Min(1, $freq / 120)\r\n    $hybridScore = [math]::Round($cfi * $normalizedFreq, 4)\r\n    \r\n    $analysisResults += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n        Token = $\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:56:40\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774382209615}}
