{"type":"message","id":"5fea778a","parentId":"a89e2354","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:56:52.792Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_vul32tjln869_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Hybrid CFIÃ—Freq Scoring Experiment (Strategy C)\n**Date:** 2026-03-24\n**Status:** RUNNING\n\n## Experiment Design\n\n### Hypothesis\nThe formula `score(T) = CFI(T) Ã— min(1, freq(T)/120)` will:\n- Penalize constant-format tokens (freqâ‰ˆ160, CFI=1) â†’ score â‰ˆ 1.0 Ã— 1.0 = 1.0 BUT capped at freq/120 = 160/120 = 1.33 â†’ min(1, 1.33) = 1.0 â†’ score = 1.0\n- Favor research trajectory tokens (freq<120, CFI>0.5) â†’ moderate score based on both dimensions\n- Distinguish \"for next instantiation\" from \"Phase 1\" based on frequency normalization\n\n### Formula Implementation\n```python\ndef hybrid_score(cfi, freq):\n    freq_normalized = min(1.0, freq / 120.0)\n    return cfi * freq_normalized\n```\n\n### Token Scoring Examples\n| Token | CFI | Freq | freq/120 | Hybrid Score | Classification |\n|-------|-----|------|----------|--------------|----------------|\n| \"for next instantiation\" | 1.00 | 160 | 1.33â†’1.0 | 1.00 | Constant (penalize) |\n| \"pulse\" | 1.00 | 160 | 1.0 | 1.00 | Constant (penalize) |\n| \"completed at:\" | 1.00 | 160 | 1.0 | 1.00 | Constant (penalize) |\n| \"Phase 1\" | 0.96 | 136 | 1.13â†’1.0 | 0.96 | Trajectory (allow) |\n| \"research\" | 0.75 | 80 | 0.67 | 0.50 | Trajectory (allow) |\n| \"architecture\" | 0.60 | 40 | 0.33 | 0.20 | Trajectory (allow) |\n\n### Key Insight\nThe min(1, freq/120) caps the frequency contribution, so even freq=160 tokens score at most 1.0 on the frequency axis, but they still get the CFI bonus. Waitâ€”that's not right for penalizing constants.\n\n### Revised Formula Logic\nActually, we want HIGH scores for research trajectory tokens and LOW scores for constants. Let's reconsider:\n\nIf freq(T) = 160 (constants):\n- min(1, 160/120) = 1.0\n- CFI(constants) â‰ˆ 1.0\n- score = 1.0 Ã— 1.0 = 1.0 (HIGH)\n\nIf freq(T) = 40 (research tokens):\n- min(1, 40/120) = 0.33\n- CFI(research) â‰ˆ 0.60\n- score = 0.60 Ã— 0.33 = 0.20 (LOW)\n\nThis is BACKWARDS. High scores go to constants.\n\n### Corrected Formula for Penalizing Constants\nWe want constants to score LOW:\n```python\ndef hybrid_score(cfi, freq):\n    freq_penalty = min(1.0, freq / 120.0)\n    return cfi * (1.0 - freq_penalty)  # Low freq â†’ high score, High freq â†’ low score\n```\n\nNow:\n- freq=160: score = 1.0 Ã— (1 - 1.0) = 0.0 (PENALIZED)\n- freq=40: score = 0.6 Ã— (1 - 0.33) = 0.6 Ã— 0.67 = 0.40 (REWARDED)\n\n### Final Formula\n```python\ndef hybrid_score(cfi, freq):\n    \"\"\"\n    score(T) = CFI(T) Ã— (1 - min(1, freq(T)/120))\n    \n    High CFI + Low freq = HIGH score (research trajectory)\n    High CFI + High freq = LOW score (constant format)\n    \"\"\"\n    freq_normalized = min(1.0, freq / 120.0)\n    return cfi * (1.0 - freq_normalized)\n```\n\n## Experiment Results (TBD)\nWill run on 200 pulses, 80/20 train/test split.\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 14:42:02\n\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# CFI Hybrid Scoring Experiment (Strategy C)\n# Testing: score(T) = CFI(T) Ã— min(1, freq(T)/120)\n\n## Hypothesis\nThe hybrid formula should:\n- De-weight constant-format tokens (freqâ‰ˆ160, CFI=1.00 â†’ scoreâ‰ˆ1.0 Ã— 1.0 = 1.0, but freq/120=1.33 capped at 1.0)\n- Properly score research trajectory tokens (freq=60, CFI=0.7 â†’ score=0.7 Ã— 0.5 = 0.35)\n- Better distinguish signal from metaprogramming noise\n\n## Method\n- 200 pulses, 80/20 train/test split\n- Strategy A: Binary thresholds (CFI â‰¥ 0.5 AND freq âˆˆ [3, 120))\n- Strategy C: Hybrid score(T) = CFI(T) Ã— min(1, freq(T)/120)\n- Metric: Precision, Recall, F1 for identifying \"important\" tokens\n\n## Pending\n- [ ] Implement scoring formulas\n- [ ] Run on pulse corpus\n- [ ] Compare precision/recall curves\r\n\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# CFI Hybrid Scoring Experiment - Strategy C Validation\nGenerated: 2026-03-24\n\n## Objective\nTest hypothesis: `score(T) = CFI(T) Ã— min(1, freq(T)/120)` distinguishes:\n- Constant format (freqâ‰ˆ160, CFIâ‰ˆ1, scoreâ‰ˆ1.0) â†’ metaprogramming artifact\n- Research trajectory (freq<120, CFI>0.5, score>0.4) â†’ true causal content\n\n## Experiment Design\n- Dataset: 200 pulses from corpus\n- Train/Test split: 80/20\n- Metric: Precision and recall for research trajectory identification\n\n## Token Categories (from CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md)\n| Token | Freq | CFI | Score | Classification |\n|-------|------|-----|-------|----------------|\n| \"for next instantiation\" | 160 | 1.00 | 1.00 | constant-format (expected to filter) |\n| \"pulse\" | 160 | 1.00 | 1.00 | constant-format (expected to filter) |\n| \"completed at:\" | 160 | 1.00 | 1.00 | constant-format (expected to filter) |\n| \"Phase 1\" | 136 | 0.96 | 0.96 | research trajectory (KEEP) |\n| \"Phase 0\" | 85 | 0.89 | 0.74 | research trajectory (KEEP) |\n| \"CFI\" | 112 | 0.72 | 0.60 | research trajectory (KEEP) |\n| \"architecture\" | 45 | 0.68 | 0.23 | research trajectory (KEEP) |\n\n## Scoring Formula\n\n\n## Hypothesis Test\nIf score > 0.4 â†’ classify as research trajectory\nExpected result:\n- Constant format (freq=160, CFI=1): score=1.0 (BUT these should be manually tagged)\n- Research trajectory (freq<120, CFI>0.5): score > 0.4 (KEEP)\n\n## KEY INSIGHT\nThe hybrid scoring does NOT filter constant-format tokens (they score high).\nThese need a SEPARATE filter: freq >= 150 as \"metaprogramming contamination\".\nFinal filter: (score > 0.4) AND (freq < 150)\n\"\r\n\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# Strategy C: Hybrid CFIÃ—Freq Scoring Experiment\n\n## Hypothesis\nThe formula `score(T) = CFI(T) Ã— min(1, freq(T)/120)` will:\n- Penalize constant-format tokens (freqâ‰ˆ160, CFI=1.0): score â‰ˆ 1.0 Ã— 1.0 = 1.0 (BUT capped at 1.0 means we need freqâ‰¥120)\n- Actually: score = 1.0 Ã— min(1, 160/120) = 1.0 Ã— 0.87 = 0.87\n- Reward research trajectory tokens (freq=80, CFI=0.8): score = 0.8 Ã— 0.67 = 0.53\n- Penalize rare tokens (freq=3, CFI=0.6): score = 0.6 Ã— 0.025 = 0.015\n\n## Problem Identified\nThe min(1, freq/120) caps at 1.0 for freqâ‰¥120, meaning constant-format tokens get score â‰ˆ 0.87-1.0.\nThis DOES NOT distinguish them from research tokens (freq=136, CFI=0.96) â†’ score = 0.96.\n\n## Revised Formula\n\n\nThis adds a hard cutoff at freq=150 to exclude constant-format tokens entirely.\n\n## Experiment Protocol\n1. Extract CFI and frequency for all tokens from pulse corpus\n2. Compute three scoring methods:\n   - A: CFI â‰¥ 0.5 (baseline)\n   - B: CFI â‰¥ 0.5 AND 3 â‰¤ freq < 120 (three-dimensional filter)\n   - C: score = CFI Ã— min(1, freq/120) AND freq < 150 (hybrid)\n3. Evaluate on 200 pulses (160 train / 40 test)\n4. Metrics: precision, recall, F1 against human-identified research tokens\r\n\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# CFI×Freq Hybrid Scoring Experiment - Strategy C\n\n**Created:** 2026-03-24\n**Status:** DESIGNED - Ready to run\n\n## Hypothesis\nHybrid score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) will:\n- De-weight constant-format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1.00 → score≈1.0 but normalized)\n- Preserve research tokens (freq<120, CFI>0.5 → score scales with CFI)\n- NOT need binary thresholds\n\n## Test Design\n1. **Dataset:** Same 200 pulses, 80/20 split\n2. **Comparison:** Hybrid scores vs binary thresholds (CFI≥0.5, freq∈[3,120))\n3. **Validation:** Manual inspection of top-scored tokens\n\n## Expected Outcome\n| Token Type | Freq | CFI | Binary Pass | Hybrid Score |\n|------------|------|-----|-------------|--------------|\n| \"for next instantiation\" | 160 | 1.00 | ✗ (freq≥120) | 1.00 |\n| \"Phase 1\" | 136 | 0.96 | ✗ (freq≥120) | 0.80 |\n| \"architecture\" | 45 | 0.72 | ✓ | 0.27 |\n| \"compression\" | 23 | 0.65 | ✓ | 0.12 |\n\n## Key Metric\nDoes hybrid scoring push research tokens (freq 30-120) above constant-format noise floor?\n\n**Run command:**\r\n\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# CFI×Freq Hybrid Scoring Experiment\n**Date:** 2026-03-24\n**Type:** Strategy C - Hybrid Scoring\n**Goal:** Test if score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) distinguishes constant-format from research trajectory\n\n## Experiment Design\n\n### Hypothesis\nThe hybrid formula will:\n1. **Dampen constant-format tokens**: score(\"for next instantiation\") = 1.0 × min(1, 160/120) = 1.0 (still high!)\n2. **Preserve research tokens**: score(\"Phase 1\") = 0.96 × min(1, 136/120) = 0.96 (unchanged)\n3. **Reward mid-frequency causal tokens**: score(\"temporal attention\") = 0.7 × min(1, 40/120) = 0.7 × 0.33 = 0.23\n\n**Problem detected:** The formula still doesn't penalize freq=160 tokens enough!\n\n### Revised Formula\nTo truly separate constant-format from research:\n\n\n### Test Plan\n1. Extract all tokens from 200 pulses\n2. Compute: CFI(T), freq(T), hybrid_score(T)\n3. Compare token distributions across three categories:\n   - **Constant-format** (expected: freq>140, CFI>0.95)\n   - **Research trajectory** (expected: 3≤freq≤120, CFI>0.5)\n   - **Noise** (expected: freq<3 OR freq>140 AND CFI<0.5)\n4. Evaluate precision/recall vs ground truth from Strategy A/B\n\n## Results (In Progress)\n*To be filled after running on pulse corpus*\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774382212790}}
{"type":"message","id":"2c3a6474","parentId":"5fea778a","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:57:00.165Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a good picture. The pulse ran and created a mutation file. Let me also check the proposed mutation file to understand what changes were proposed.\n\nActually, I have enough to summarize. Let me just report what happened.","thinkingSignature":"563ff3f7aa586ade89647d250ebb62018934e03143261cf4d3c19c7b3c1ef039"},{"type":"text","text":"\n---\n\n## Pulse Summary — 2026-03-24 15:56\n\n**What happened:** The pulse analyzed the CFI compression findings and proposed a new hybrid scoring experiment. The key insight from the prior pulse cycle: the formula `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` was found to be **backwards** — it actually rewards constant-format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1 → score≈1.0) rather than penalizing them.\n\n**Correction identified:** The revised formula should be `score(T) = CFI(T) × (1 - min(1, freq(T)/120))` — inverting the frequency term so that high-frequency constants get penalized (score→0) and mid-frequency research tokens get rewarded.\n\n**Proposed mutation:** Created `research/cfi_hybrid_experiment.ps1` implementing Strategy C (hybrid scoring) vs binary thresholds for comparison on 200 pulses.\n\n**Token category findings from synthesis:**\n\n| Token | Freq | CFI | Issue |\n|-------|------|-----|-------|\n| \"for next instantiation\" | 160 | 1.00 | Constant-format artifact |\n| \"pulse\" | 160 | 1.00 | Constant-format artifact |\n| \"Phase 1\" | 136 | 0.96 | Research trajectory ✓ |\n| \"architecture\" | 45 | 0.68 | Research trajectory ✓ |\n\n**Status:** The hybrid experiment design is ready but hasn't been executed yet. Need to run the experiment script to validate the revised formula against the corpus."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":6581,"output":372,"cacheRead":12245,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":19198,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774382212793}}
